{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-add-magento-2-terms-and-conditions-checkbox/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How To Add Magento 2 Terms And Conditions Checkbox","content":"\n<p><br><a href=\"https://business.adobe.com/in/products/magento/open-source.html\">Magento 2</a> is an advanced e-commerce platform that offers businesses a flexible and expandable solution for managing their online stores. When it comes to running an online store, one crucial aspect to consider is establishing clear terms and conditions that customers must agree to before completing a purchase. These terms and conditions serve to safeguard both your business and your customers, minimizing the potential for legal conflicts down the line.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, the checkout process in Magento 2 does not include a checkbox for accepting the terms and conditions. However, incorporating this feature is a straightforward procedure that can be accomplished in just a few steps. In this blog post, we will guide you through the process of seamlessly learning <strong><em>How to add Magento 2 Terms and Conditions Checkbox.</em></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Steps to Add Magento 2 Terms and Conditions Checkbox</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Create a New Checkbox Attribute</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step in adding a <strong>Magento 2 terms and conditions checkbox</strong> to your Magento 2 store is to create a new checkbox attribute. This attribute will be used to store the customer&#8217;s agreement to the terms and conditions. To create a new attribute, follow these steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Log in to your Magento 2 admin panel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Navigate to Stores &gt; Attributes &gt; Customer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Click the Add New Attribute button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Fill in the required fields, such as Attribute Code and Default Value.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Under the Catalog Input Type for Store Owner dropdown, select Yes/No.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">6. Click the Save Attribute button to create the new attribute.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><br><br><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained  inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:624px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;289&#x27;%20width=&#x27;624&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 624px) 624px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/5eb1d929db5747490192b33b2057677e/dfd15a340840b12c94cc57c093c57c5f/082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png&amp;a=w%3D156%26h%3D72%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-06-15T10%3A20%3A36\" data-srcset=\"/_gatsby/image/5eb1d929db5747490192b33b2057677e/dfd15a340840b12c94cc57c093c57c5f/082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png&amp;a=w%3D156%26h%3D72%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-06-15T10%3A20%3A36 156w,/_gatsby/image/5eb1d929db5747490192b33b2057677e/dc64605831263dcce1653475e2134a4f/082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93