605831263dcce1653475e2134a4f/082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png&a=w%3D312%26h%3D145%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-06-15T10%3A20%3A36 312w,/_gatsby/image/5eb1d929db5747490192b33b2057677e/1f76fd01fd54e5c2f805ee37d54775d7/082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png&a=w%3D624%26h%3D289%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-06-15T10%3A20%3A36 624w,/_gatsby/image/5eb1d929db5747490192b33b2057677e/a191abafe91bd527703c8ee6d020892d/082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F082530b38c5d0f53616f142a45e19e93.png&a=w%3D1248%26h%3D579%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-06-15T10%3A20%3A36 1248w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 624px) 624px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":624,\"height\":289},\"alt\":\"\",\"className\":\" inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"1\"}</script></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Step 2: Add the Checkbox to the Checkout Page</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step is to add the checkbox to the checkout page. To do this, follow these steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Navigate to Stores &gt; Configuration &gt; Sales &gt; Checkout.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Under the Checkout Options section, find the Enable Terms and Conditions checkbox and set it to Yes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Under the Terms and Conditions section, enter the text of your terms and conditions in the respective fields.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Under the Checkbox Text field, enter the text you want to display next to the checkbox.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Under the Checkbox Checked by Default dropdown, select No.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>6. Under the Checkbox Custom Attribute field, enter the attribute code you created in Step 1.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>7. Click the Save Config button to save your changes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><br><br><div data-gatsby-im